This repository contains the open standard type definitions for the Lattice
Protocol: Module, Lattice, and Dataset. These types are licensed under MIT
to enable interoperability and adoption across the federated AI ecosystem.

The aDNA type system is intentionally open — network effects require open
adoption. The protocol implementation that executes these types is separately
licensed under BSL 1.1 in the lattice-protocol repository.

